 A 29-year-old nursing mother, identified simply as Tawa, and her five-month-old baby have been killed by generator fumes in Owo, Ondo State. It was gathered that the tragic incident which occurred on Friday, March 10, also left Tawa’s husband hospitalized. The deceased, an employee of the Federal Medical Centre (FMC) & her husband were said to have purchased the generator last Monday, just 3 days before the unfortunate incident. TheNation reports that the couple purchased the generator on Monday & left it on while they went to bed on Thursday evening. Witnesses said the family was found when their apartment was brok£n into after they did not report for work on Friday. Tawa’s elder sister who could not find the couple at their places of work was said to have raised the alarm. It was gathered that some co-workers went to their house in company of the elder sister & br%ke into the apartments where they discovered the family.